Kobe had one gear: Better.

The Kobe 9 Elite High Protro ‘Halo’ is available 8.23 on SNKRS in select regions. The Low makes its return on 9.19.

Every team wants to beat the odds. One team is the odds. 

The reign of @teamusa Men’s Basketball continues at the @olympics.

#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

Winning Isn’t For Everyone. It’s for those who do whatever it takes. 

You can’t win them all, but you should sure as hell try. Bring on the odds, play like you mean it. Because if you don’t want to win, congrats. You’ve already lost.

#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024 @olympics

No distance too far. No record unbreakable. ❤️‍🔥 

One year ago, @sifanhassan had never run a competitive marathon. Today, she broke the @olympics record to take home gold. She is now the first person on earth to win three distance medals at two consecutive Olympic games.

#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

You can’t stop the reign.

There’s no argument, @dianataurasi’s resume is goated. She’s been one of the best players in the world for over two decades. A 6th gold medal would make her THE most decorated basketball player in @Olympics history.

#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

Even worthy opponents can’t take their crown. 👑

That’s eight straight @olympics gold medals for @teamusa Women’s Basketball.

#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

2014 design. Modern day technology. You’re welcome.

BZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZ.

Inspired by hip-hop history, @nike collaborated with legendary artist and cultural icon @futuradosmil to design a collection for the first class of competitive breakers.

Athletes from Team USA, Team Japan, and Team Korea will sport the pieces during the games.

Her Royal Flyness 👑

A true force of nature—to the point that nature trains with him.
 
New colorways of the #AirMaxDn are available now to help you feel the unreal. Tap the link in @nikesportswear’s bio to shop now.

Double the distance. Double the gold.
 
From the 5k to the 10k, there’s no distance @beatrice.chebet91 can’t conquer. With her 10,000m @Olympics win, she becomes the first Kenyan woman ever to earn gold in the event.
 
#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

Throw down for the crown.

Never thought Hip Hop would take it this far? @gfc_ami did. She just made history by bringing home the first-ever @Olympics gold medal for Breaking.

#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

@kimiya.alizade knows the true meaning of loss. Yet every time she steps onto the mat, she carries with her an insatiable desire to win.

@olympics #WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

The world follows in their footsteps. 

The USA women’s relay team left it all on the track to take @Olympics gold in the 4x100m. 

#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

🤫 @tebogo_letsile_ silences the competition.

Tonight he claims Botswana’s first ever @olympics gold. 🇧🇼🥇#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

Third time’s a charm 🍁🍁🍁

After their team took bronze in Rio and silver in Tokyo, @kingsleysc and @_jeromeblake helped torch the competition to secure gold in the @olympics 4x100m relay.

#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

When @keely.hodgkinson moves to the front, it becomes a race for second.  Tonight was one more stride in her pursuit of @olympics greatness.

#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

You miss 100% of the shots you don’t take.
But against @wemby, you’ll be lucky if you get to take any at all.
#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024 @Olympics

#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

Swimmer @ariarnetitmus_ and fencers @olgakharlan and @leetothekiefer are packing a little heavier on the way home from the Paris @olympics.

A lifetime of work, in seconds.

Down in the standings with only one chance left, he landed the best trick and biggest score of the night to secure back-to-back @olympics gold.

#WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

The Winner’s Curse.

Every ring. Every medal. Every record. His hunger is insatiable. Doesn’t matter if it’s his 1st or 4th @olympics games, LeBron James has no choice but to try to win again. #WinningIsntForEveryone #Paris2024

Was the Air Max Plus inspired by a Florida vacation? 🍹@annierau and Nike Air-storian Matt Williams crack the case in this week’s episode of ‘Truth or Air’: a series about the truths and myths behind iconic Air Max designs and the all-new Air Max Dn.

The all-new Air Max Dn stars in the final episode of ‘Truth or Air,’ a show where @annierau and Nike Air-storian Matt Williams investigate the truths and myths behind iconic Air Max designs.

On behalf of Nike Sportswear and the Department of Nike Archives, thanks for watching.📺 And check our highlights for any episodes you missed.

From leather leisure shoes in the 1980s to the Air Max Dn today, lifestyle footwear has come along way at Nike. And the Air Max line in particular owes a lot to the underdog influence of the Air Safari print.

Swipe to explore the influence of the Air Safari print on the Air Max line with artifacts from the Department of Nike Archives.🔍

Airphoria is back with a new experience in @fortnite. Enter the Dn Dimension on March 26 💫

Is Infrared the OG Air Max 90 colorway? We visited the Department of Nike Archives to find out in our new series, ‘Truth or Air.’ 

The Air Max 90 (f.k.a. Air Max III) was released in four colorways in 1990: Hot Coral-Crystal Blue, Concord-Fluorescent Pink, Laser Blue and Radiant Red, later known as Infrared.

Swipe for a peek at the DNA Artifacts 👀 including a sketch by Tinker Hatfield.

Ahead of the launch of the all-new Air Max Dn, Nike Sportswear and the Department of Nike Archives present ‘Truth or Air’: a new series exploring the truths and myths behind the iconic Air Max designs that paved the way. 

This week, host @annierau from @depthsofwikipedia joins Nike Air-storian Matt Williams to investigate real Nike artifacts from the archive and crack the mystery surrounding the Air Max 90 Infrared.

Keep an eye on our feed for more on the history and influence of #AirMax colorways.👀

Who’s ready for Paris? We are.
